    "body": "That works indeed but the point of my demo was to show this general behavior.\n\nIf you have an application that hides the dock icon when no more windows are visible (e. g. to keep living in the systray) and then re-shows the dock icon when a window gets opened, you canâ€™t really avoid the behavior unless you use something like the following which is kinda hacky:\n\n``` javascript\napp.dock.show()\nsetInterval(win.show, 250)\n```\n"
