    "updated_at": "2016-09-26T07:21:19Z",
    "body": "OS X does not really support showing/hiding dock icon dynamically, it is done by switching the app between foreground and background modes, and unfortunately by using the APIs provided by Apple this glitch is not avoidable. So your only solution is to avoid doing this, or just live with the side effect.\n\nI'm closing this as won't fix since there does not seem to have a way to fix it.\n"
